#. <section class="sutta" id="sn1.40"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn1.40:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 1"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 1"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn1.40:0.2"
msgid "4. Satullapakāyikavagga"
msgstr "4. The Satullapa Group"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 40. Dutiyapajjunnadhītusuttaṃ → cullapajjunnadhītusuttaṃ (bj) | pajjunnadhītusuttaṃ (2) (s1) | pajjunnadhītā (2) (pts1)
msgctxt "sn1.40:0.3"
msgid "40. Dutiyapajjunnadhītusuttaṃ"
msgstr "40. With Pajjunna’s Daughter (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.63"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "sn1.40:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. </span>
msgctxt "sn1.40:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof."

#. VAR: cūḷakokanadā → cullakokanadā (bj, s1-3, km, pts2)
msgctxt "sn1.40:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho cūḷakokanadā pajjunnassa dhītā abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ mahāvanaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi."
msgstr "Then, late at night, the beautiful Kokanadā the Younger, Pajjunna’s daughter, lighting up the entire Great Wood, went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side,"

msgctxt "sn1.40:1.4"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho sā devatā cūḷakokanadā pajjunnassa dhītā bhagavato santike imā gāthāyo abhāsi:"
msgstr "and recited these verses in the Buddha’s presence:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.40:2.1"
msgid "“Idhāgamā vijjupabhāsavaṇṇā,"
msgstr "“Kokanadā, Pajjunna’s daughter, came here,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.40:2.2"
msgid "Kokanadā pajjunnassa dhītā;"
msgstr "beautiful as a flash of lightning."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.40:2.3"
msgid "Buddhañca dhammañca namassamānā,"
msgstr "Revering the Buddha and the teaching,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.40:2.4"
msgid "Gāthācimā atthavatī abhāsi."
msgstr "she spoke these verses full of meaning."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.31"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.40:3.1"
msgid "Bahunāpi kho taṃ vibhajeyyaṃ,"
msgstr "The teaching is such that"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.40:3.2"
msgid "Pariyāyena tādiso dhammo;"
msgstr "I could analyze it in many different ways."

#. <br>
#. VAR: Saṃkhittamatthaṃ → saṃkhittamattaṃ (bj, mr)
msgctxt "sn1.40:3.3"
msgid "Saṃkhittamatthaṃ lapayissāmi,"
msgstr "However, I will state the meaning in brief"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.40:3.4"
msgid "Yāvatā me manasā pariyattaṃ."
msgstr "as far as I have learned it by heart."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.64"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.40:4.1"
msgid "Pāpaṃ na kayirā vacasā manasā,"
msgstr "You should never do anything bad"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.40:4.2"
msgid "Kāyena vā kiñcana sabbaloke;"
msgstr "by speech or mind or body in all the world."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.40:4.3"
msgid "Kāme pahāya satimā sampajāno,"
msgstr "Having given up sensual pleasures, mindful and aware,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.40:4.4"
msgid "Dukkhaṃ na sevetha anatthasaṃhitan”ti."
msgstr "you shouldn’t keep doing what’s painful and pointless.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn1.40:4.5"
msgid "Satullapakāyikavaggo catuttho."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.40:5.1"
msgid "Sabbhimaccharinā sādhu,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.40:5.2"
msgid "na santujjhānasaññino;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.40:5.3"
msgid "Saddhā samayo sakalikaṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.40:5.4"
msgid "ubho pajjunnadhītaroti."
msgstr ""
